the Universal access to internet. and for that I reckon if social medias (e.g facebook and twitter, etc) are still restricted here, I think it will take time to integrate Moringa in my diet.

Also, my dream is to become a farmer and to live a self sustainable life in terms of foods and other important things, so I could teach this to the youth and those who are willing to learn, to become a leader on the way the agriculture/food and the environment will be oriented.

Here, we have a century old interactive radio that is still used by resource centres, libraries, schools and also by other nurses and doctors for high level hygiene education. To develop this knowledge and to integrate moringa to childs allowing them to try and to learn, I think it would be great opportunity to introduce this giant resource. The broadcast could be done in many different means (nowadays it can be done live without wasting time to prepare and reload etc.).

So if someday you could find a mobile team to bring Moringa to Guinea, be sure that I would be more than happy to join and help to build something stronger than I am.

best regards,
Albert
